The paper deals with visual recognition and proposes a framework for context-aware interaction recognition. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses word2vec to encode context, which is a common technique in Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning (ML), indicating that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of classifiers, which is a common technique in Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Multimedia (cs.MM), further supporting the possibility of these sub-categories.
